Trichet, Bernanke Topped By Hong Kong’s Chan for Pay

-- B y   S o p h i e   L e u n g
-- 
2011-04-21T08:29:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/trichet-bernanke-topped-by-hong-kong-s-chan-for-pay-1-.html
Hong Kong  Monetary Authority
Chief Executive  Norman Chan  earned more than European Central
Bank President Jean-Claude Trichet and Federal Reserve
Chairman Ben S. Bernanke last year.  Chan was paid HK$7.5 million ($965,000), plus HK$868,000
in benefits, according to the HKMA’s annual report published
today. Trichet earned 367,863 euros ($513,000), while
Bernanke was paid $199,700.  Bank of Japan Governor Masaaki Shirakawa’s salary was
34.4 million yen ($420,000) for the year ending March 31.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sophie Leung in Hong Kong at 
 sleung59@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Panckhurst in Hong Kong at 
 ppanckhurst@bloomberg.net  